==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek exo, outside, from ex, out of, and from Greek politika, from neuter plural of politikos political.

===Noun===
'''exopolitics'''  {{p}}

# the art or science of government as concerned with guiding or influencing governmental policy toward extraterrestrial phenomena and extraterrestrial beings.
# exopolitical actions, practices, or policies.
# the exopolitical opinions or sympathies of a person.
# the total complex of relations between the human race and non-human, intelligent beings.

